  "local_port": 35812,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I add more than one WordPress site in Godaddy's Deluxe hosting plan?",
  "response": "Adding multiple WordPress sites to GoDaddy\u2019s Deluxe Hosting plan is a straightforward process. The Deluxe plan typically supports hosting multiple websites, allowing you to manage several WordPress installations under a single account. Below is a step-by-step guide to help you set up additional WordPress sites:\n\n### **Prerequisites:**\n\n1. **Domains:** Ensure you have registered the domain names you want to use for each WordPress site. If you haven\u2019t registered them yet, you can do so through GoDaddy or any other domain registrar.\n\n2. **Access to GoDaddy Account:** You should have your GoDaddy account credentials handy to access the hosting dashboard.\n\n### **Step-by-Step Guide:**\n\n#### **1. Log in to Your GoDaddy Account**\n\n- Navigate to [GoDaddy.com](https://www.godaddy.com/) and click on the **\"Sign In\"** button located at the top right corner.\n- Enter your username and password to access your account dashboard.\n\n#### **2. Access Your Hosting Dashboard**\n\n- Once logged in, click on your **username** in the top right corner and select **\"My Products\"** from the dropdown menu.\n- Under the **\"Web Hosting\"** section, locate your **Deluxe Hosting plan** and click on **\"Manage\"**.\n\n#### **3. Enter the Hosting Control Panel (cPanel)**\n\n- In the hosting dashboard, look for an option to access **cPanel**. This might be labeled as **\"cPanel Admin\"** or similar.\n- Click on it to open the cPanel interface where you can manage your hosting settings.\n\n#### **4. Add an Addon Domain for Your New Website**\n\nAn **Addon Domain** allows you to host additional domains (websites) on your existing hosting account.\n\n- In cPanel, locate the **\"Domains\"** section and click on **\"Addon Domains\"**.\n  \n- **Fill in the Addon Domain Details:**\n  - **New Domain Name:** Enter the domain name you wish to add (e.g., `newsite.com`).\n  - **Subdomain/FTP Username:** This is usually auto-filled. You can leave it as default or modify if needed.\n  - **Document Root:** This specifies the folder where the new website's files will reside (e.g., `public_html/newsite`). You can customize this or leave the default value.\n  \n- **Add the Domain:**\n  - After filling in the details, click the **\"Add Domain\"** button. This action creates the necessary directory structure for your new website.\n\n#### **5. Point Your Domain to GoDaddy Hosting (If Necessary)**\n\nIf your domain is registered with another registrar, ensure that its DNS settings point to GoDaddy\u2019s servers. If the domain is registered with GoDaddy, this is typically handled automatically.\n\n- **DNS Settings:**\n  - Go to the domain registrar\u2019s dashboard.\n  - Update the **Nameservers** to GoDaddy\u2019s default nameservers or as specified in your hosting details.\n  - Save the changes. DNS propagation can take up to 48 hours, but it usually completes within a few hours.\n\n#### **6. Install WordPress on the Addon Domain**\n\nNow that the domain is set up, install WordPress on it.\n\n- **Using cPanel\u2019s WordPress Installer:**\n  - In cPanel, navigate to the **\"Softaculous Apps Installer\"** or **\"WordPress Manager\"** under the **\"Apps\"** section.\n  \n- **Start the Installation:**\n  - Click on the **\"Install\"** button for WordPress.\n  \n- **Configure Installation Settings:**\n  - **Choose Protocol:** Select `http://` or `https://` depending on your SSL setup.\n  - **Choose Domain:** From the dropdown, select the addon domain you just added (e.g., `newsite.com`).\n  \n  - **Directory:** Leave this blank to install WordPress in the root of the addon domain (`newsite.com`) or specify a folder if you prefer.\n  \n  - **Site Settings:**\n    - **Site Name:** Enter the name for your new WordPress site.\n    - **Site Description:** Provide a brief description; this can be changed later from the WordPress dashboard.\n  \n  - **Admin Account:**\n    - **Admin Username:** Choose a unique username for logging into WordPress.\n    - **Admin Password:** Create a strong password.\n    - **Admin Email:** Provide an email address for administrative purposes.\n  \n  - **Choose Language:** Select your preferred language for WordPress.\n  \n  - **Select Plugins/Themes (Optional):** Some installers allow you to auto-install recommended plugins or themes.\n  \n- **Advanced Options (Optional):**\n  - Customize database name, table prefix, or other advanced settings if needed.\n  \n- **Install WordPress:**\n  - After configuring all settings, click the **\"Install\"** button.\n  - Wait for the installation process to complete. Once done, you'll receive a confirmation with your WordPress site\u2019s admin URL.\n\n#### **7. Repeat for Additional WordPress Sites**\n\nFor each additional WordPress site you want to add:\n\n1. **Add a new Addon Domain** following steps 4 and 5.\n2. **Install WordPress** on the new addon domain following step 6.\n\n#### **8. Manage Your WordPress Sites**\n\n- **Accessing Admin Dashboards:**\n  - Each WordPress installation will have its own admin dashboard accessible via `http://yourdomain.com/wp-admin`.\n  \n- **Updating and Maintaining:**\n  - Regularly update WordPress core, themes, and plugins for security and performance.\n  \n- **Backup:**\n  - Implement regular backups using plugins or GoDaddy\u2019s backup solutions to safeguard your sites.\n\n### **Additional Tips:**\n\n- **SSL Certificates:**\n  - Ensure each addon domain has an SSL certificate. GoDaddy often provides free SSL for addon domains, or you can purchase them as needed.\n  \n- **Resource Management:**\n  - Monitor your hosting resources (like disk space and bandwidth) to ensure optimal performance across all your sites.\n  \n- **Support:**\n  - If you encounter issues or need assistance, contact GoDaddy\u2019s support for personalized help.\n\n### **Alternatives:**\n\n- **Managed WordPress Hosting:**\n  - If you plan to host multiple WordPress sites, consider GoDaddy\u2019s Managed WordPress Hosting, which is optimized for WordPress and may offer better performance and additional features tailored for WordPress sites.\n  \n- **WordPress Multisite:**\n  - Alternatively, you can set up a WordPress Multisite network to manage multiple sites from a single WordPress installation. This method is more advanced and suitable if you want centralized management, but each site shares the same WordPress installation and resources.\n\n### **Conclusion**\n\nBy following the steps above, you can efficiently add multiple WordPress sites to your GoDaddy Deluxe Hosting plan. Whether you\u2019re managing personal blogs, business websites, or portfolios, GoDaddy\u2019s hosting environment provides the flexibility and tools needed to maintain multiple WordPress installations seamlessly.\n\nIf you encounter any issues or need further customization, don\u2019t hesitate to reach out to GoDaddy\u2019s customer support or refer to their [official help documentation](https://www.godaddy.com/help/manage-websites-1926).",
